==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Restitute
<hw>Res"ti*tute</hw> <pr>(r?s"t?*t?t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>restitutus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>restituere</ets>; pref.
<ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>statuere</ets> to put, place. See
<er>Statute</er>.]</ety> <def>To restore to a former state.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Dyer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Restitute</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Restitute
<hw>Res"ti*tute</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That which is restored or
offered in place of something; a substitute.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Restitution</ent>⟦br⟧
